
Overview of noun lather

The noun lather has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) soapsuds, suds, lather -- (the froth produced by soaps or detergents)
2. fret, stew, sweat, lather, swither -- (agitation resulting from active worry; "don't get in a stew"; "he's in a sweat about exams")
3. lather -- (a workman who puts up laths)
4. lather -- (the foam resulting from excessive sweating (as on a horse))

Overview of verb lather

The verb lather has 4 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
